quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  71,21,"Finally, Noah submitted: \"O Lord! My people have disobeyed me, and followed those chiefs whose wealth and children have added to them nothing but loss"
  71,22,They have devised an outrageous plot
  71,23,"and said to each other: 'Do not leave your gods; especially Wadd, Suwa, Yaghus, Yauq and Nasr (the names of their idols)"
  71,24,"They have already misled many, so O Lord, do not increase the wrongdoers in anything but deviation"
  71,25,Because of their wrong doings they were drowned in the great flood and made to enter the fire. They found no one besides Allah to help them
  71,26,"As Noah had prayed: \"O Lord! Do not leave a single unbeliever on the surface of the earth"
  71,27,"For if You spare any of them, they will mislead your servants and beget none but wicked unbelievers"
  71,28,"O Lord! Forgive me, my parents and every true believer who seeks refuge in my house, and all believing men and believing women. As to the wrongdoers, grant them increase in nothing but destruction"